# Generated by Cargo
# will have compiled files and executables
debug
target

# These are backup files generated by rustfmt
**/*.rs.bk

# MSVC Windows builds of rustc generate these, which store debugging information
*.pdb

# Generated by cargo mutants
# Contains mutation testing data
**/mutants.out*/

# RustRover
#  JetBrains specific template is maintained in a separate JetBrains.gitignore that can
#  be found at https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/Global/JetBrains.gitignore
#  and can be added to the global gitignore or merged into this file.  For a more nuclear
#  option (not recommended) you can uncomment the following to ignore the entire idea folder.
#.idea/
# (the Tauri shell's dist/ holds hand-written static assets and IS committed;
# only its generated wasm output is ignored — see below)
dist/
!crates/geleit-shell/dist/
crates/geleit-shell/dist/pkg/

# stray screenshots dropped in the repo root (manual images live in docs/manual/images/)
/Screenshot*.png

# never commit saved mail files (may contain personal mail)
*.eml

# ...nor screenshots of them. Spike/debug captures of real mail expose personal data (M9): keep
# them out of the repo entirely. Manual images (docs/manual/images/) are curated by hand.
/*.png

# Tauri generates these permission/capability schemas at build time from tauri.conf.json.
crates/geleit-shell/gen/schemas/

# wasm-bindgen output for the M9 cold-start spike (generated from ui/src)
spikes/wasm-coldstart/ui/pkg/
